<P N="8"><PB N="389" REF="021451_0388_0FB52656F5BC7458">8. Ah! mercy on my &s;oul! What is that? My old friend<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> gho&s;t! T<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y &s;ay, none but wicked folks walk. I wi&s;h <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> were at the bottom o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> a coal pit! La! how pale, and how <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ong his fac<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> is grown &s;ince his death. He ne|ver was h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">me. And death has improved him very much the w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ong way.&mdash;Pray, do not come near me. I wi&s;hed y<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">u very well when you were alive. But I could never abide a dead m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> ch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">k <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y jowl with me &mdash;Ah, ah, m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rcy on us' <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o ne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rer, pray! <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> it be only to take your leave of me, that you are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span">, I could have excu|&s;ed you the c<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">remony <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> heart.&mdash;Or if you&mdash; mercy <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n us&mdash;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> ne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rer <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y,&mdash;or if you have wronged any bo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y, as you alway<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ov<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d money a lit<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">le, I give you the w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rd of a frighted Chri&s;tian, I will pray, as long as you plea&s;e, for the de<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">iverance and repo&s;e of your de|parted &s;oul. My g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">od, worthy, noble friend, do, pray, di&s;appear, as ever you would wi&s;h your old friend to come to his &s;en&s;es again.
